bilingual.target: 技术的领域正在迅速增长。

bilingual.source: The company is known for its technological innovations.
bilingual.target: 这家公司以其技术的创新而闻名。

bilingual.source: The technological capabilities of this device are impressive.
bilingual.target: 这个设备的技术的能力令人印象深刻。

bilingual.source: The technological revolution has advanced medical technology.
bilingual.target: 技术革命推动了医疗技术的进步。

bilingual.source: She is studying technological trends in the automotive industry.
bilingual.target: 她正在研究汽车行业的技术的趋势。

bilingual.source: The aero industry is booming with new technological advancements.
bilingual.target: 航空的行业随着新技术的进步正在蓬勃发展。

bilingual.source: Technological advancements have greatly improved our quality of life.
bilingual.target: 技术的进步极大地提高了我们的生活质量。

bilingual.source: We need to upgrade our equipment to keep pace with technological advancements.
bilingual.target: 我们需要更新设备以跟上技术的发展。

bilingual.source: Due to technological advances, the speed of information transfer has seen rapid growth.
bilingual.target: 由于技术的进步，信息传递的速度有了快速增长。

bilingual.source: In reality, technological progress is rather less orderly.
bilingual.target: 事实上, 技术的进步很少有步调一致的情形.

yingyinNormal.en: New technological advances have seen them enter the space race with the US and Russia for the first time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 新技术的进步见证着中国进入太空竞赛的脚步，和美国、俄罗斯同台竞艺。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 生物技术；生物工艺

word_family.mean: n. 技术；工艺；工业技术；设备；机器；技术学；工艺学

examination_example.sentence: Congress or the Supreme Court could intervene to avoid trapping Internet regulation in <highlight>technological</highlight> anachronism.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 国会或最高法院可以干预，以避免互联网监管陷入技术时代错误。

examination_example.sentence: Optimists point out that <highlight>technological</highlight> upheaval has benefited workers in the past.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 乐观主义者指出，技术变革在过去曾给工人带来益处。

examination_example.sentence: In previous eras of drastic <highlight>technological</highlight> change, entrepreneurs smoothed the transition by dreaming up ways to combine labor and machines.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在以往技术剧烈变革的时代，企业家们通过想出将劳动力和机器结合起来的方法，使这种转变变得平稳。

examination_example.sentence: Fast <highlight>technological</highlight> change makes it necessary for one to constantly upgrade their skills.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 快速的技术变革使人们有必要不断提升自己的技能。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Technological</highlight> innovations, combined with good marketing, will promote the sales of these products.
